1
00:00:46,212 --> 00:00:47,236
Joe?

2
00:00:49,783 --> 00:00:52,343
Stay back. Stay back.

3
00:00:54,454 --> 00:00:58,322
Joe, I'm Phoebe MacNamara.
I'm with the Police Department.

4
00:00:59,426 --> 00:01:01,690
- Brought you a beer.
- What?

5
00:01:03,797 --> 00:01:05,526
Put it on the ledge.

6
00:01:08,802 --> 00:01:12,135
Phoebe, Tactical is moving into position.
Be careful.

7
00:01:25,485 --> 00:01:27,419
You planning on jumping?

8
00:01:29,456 --> 00:01:31,014
Don't tell me it's over a woman.

9
00:01:31,724 --> 00:01:32,918
My wife.

10
00:01:33,626 --> 00:01:35,594
Why don't you sit back down?

11
00:01:35,695 --> 00:01:37,686
Yeah. Yeah.

12
00:01:52,979 --> 00:01:55,038
So what's your wife's name?

13
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:56,840
Lori.

14
00:01:58,351 --> 00:01:59,716
She left me.

15
00:02:01,554 --> 00:02:04,148
- You really a cop?
- Yes.

16
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:07,385
She left you 'cause you were gambling?

17
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:12,057
She was all I had.

18
00:02:13,766 --> 00:02:16,667
Aren't you gonna get in trouble
for drinking?

19
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:18,968
Not if you don't jump.

20
00:02:26,579 --> 00:02:29,207
I stole $5,000 from my boss.

21
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:33,111
I met your boss.
He seems like a really nice guy.

22
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:38,223
What if I talked to him, got him
to give you time to pay the money back?

23
00:02:41,127 --> 00:02:42,560
I don't know.

24
00:02:45,532 --> 00:02:48,968
If you could talk to her right now,
what would you say?

25
00:02:53,406 --> 00:02:55,271
I guess that I'm sorry,

26
00:02:56,442 --> 00:02:59,707
that I love her, and I don't wanna lose her.

27
00:02:59,812 --> 00:03:03,680
Well, if you don't wanna lose her
and you really love her, Joe,

28
00:03:04,817 --> 00:03:08,548
you gotta hand me the gun
and get off this ledge, okay?

29
00:03:08,655 --> 00:03:12,056
Otherwise you're just leaving Lori
with a whole lot of grief and guilt.

30
00:03:12,158 --> 00:03:15,594
I don't wanna do that. It's not her fault.

31
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:17,724
Then show her that.

32
00:03:41,921 --> 00:03:43,548
Give me your hand.

33
00:03:45,191 --> 00:03:46,385
Come on.

34
00:03:59,439 --> 00:04:01,930
You'll have to go with this officer.

35
00:04:07,714 --> 00:04:12,208
Lieutenant, I am just going to pretend
you didn't give a beer to a jumper.

36
00:04:12,785 --> 00:04:14,946
- What beer, Captain?
- Exactly.

37
00:04:19,325 --> 00:04:22,021
You always go right up to guys
with guns like that?

38
00:04:22,128 --> 00:04:24,221
Only on Sundays. You pressing charges?

39
00:04:24,330 --> 00:04:27,697
No, no. Listen, I don't
want Joe to go to jail.

40
00:04:28,134 --> 00:04:30,295
He's worked for me for three years.
He's never been a problem.

41
00:04:30,403 --> 00:04:32,030
Well, he's gonna have to pay
the money back he owes you

42
00:04:32,138 --> 00:04:34,606
- for his own self- respect.
- Okay.

43
00:04:35,942 --> 00:04:36,966
Hey.

44
00:04:37,644 --> 00:04:40,579
- Let me buy you a drink.
- I just had one.

45
00:04:48,921 --> 00:04:51,856
- Carly, you ready?
- I'm ready.

46
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:54,858
It's too cold for shorts, sweetie.

47
00:04:56,763 --> 00:04:59,698
- Put your foot in. Other foot.
- Don't forget my scrunchie.

48
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,562
Okay. Shoes.

49
00:05:01,934 --> 00:05:02,958
Down there.

50
00:05:03,069 --> 00:05:05,230
I can put my shoes on all by myself, Mommy.

51
00:05:05,338 --> 00:05:08,102
Okay, you do that.
I'll see you downstairs, okay?

52
00:05:11,177 --> 00:05:13,304
- What are you doing?
- We have a leak.

53
00:05:13,413 --> 00:05:15,244
- Great.
- I've almost got her lunch made.

54
00:05:15,348 --> 00:05:17,680
- I just need to add the apple juice.
- Thanks, Mom.

55
00:05:17,784 --> 00:05:18,910
Carly!

56
00:05:19,752 --> 00:05:22,812
Carly. Come here, baby.

57
00:05:23,956 --> 00:05:25,548
There's my girl.

58
00:05:25,658 --> 00:05:27,717
- We have a leak.
- Yes, we do.

59
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:30,121
There we go. Let's get your shoe on.

60
00:05:30,229 --> 00:05:31,821
Put your foot to the back.

61
00:05:31,931 --> 00:05:35,890
- I want my froggy backpack.
- Well, I can't find it, sweetheart.

62
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,469
Hey, Mom, will you flag down
the bus for me?

63
00:05:37,570 --> 00:05:39,731
I haven't got time to drive her
if she doesn't make it.

64
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:42,137
Got a training session at 8:00.

65
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,443
What's wrong?

66
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:48,940
Grandma can't go on the porch anymore.

67
00:05:49,615 --> 00:05:51,082
Since when?

68
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:53,209
I've got it. I've got it.

69
00:05:54,153 --> 00:05:57,122
- Come on.
- Here's your lunch. Into the froggy.

70
00:05:58,591 --> 00:05:59,956
There you go.

71
00:06:00,793 --> 00:06:02,556
- Big girl.
- Come on.

72
00:06:02,662 --> 00:06:05,290
- Hold my hand.
- Here we go. There we go.

73
00:06:05,398 --> 00:06:07,025
We missed the bus.

74
00:06:09,969 --> 00:06:11,960
You can catch it on Colby.

75
00:06:13,673 --> 00:06:16,642
Can you come to help with my class today?

76
00:06:16,743 --> 00:06:18,404
I can't, sweetie. I gotta go to work.

77
00:06:18,511 --> 00:06:20,911
Well, all the other mommies do,
but you never come.

78
00:06:21,013 --> 00:06:23,106
Next week, okay? I promise.

79
00:06:24,484 --> 00:06:27,612
Come on. You got your backpack?
Watch your head.

80
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,627
We need a new car.

81
00:06:58,384 --> 00:07:01,148
Okay, today we're gonna
continue our discussion

82
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:03,745
about your role as first responders.

83
00:07:03,856 --> 00:07:04,982
Ma'am?

84
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:08,185
I was wondering about
that jumper yesterday.

85
00:07:08,294 --> 00:07:11,457
You broke a lot of your own
rules of negotiation.

86
00:07:12,198 --> 00:07:14,063
It's Lieutenant, Officer Meeks.

87
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:16,499
And if you'd been paying attention
over the past two weeks,

88
00:07:16,602 --> 00:07:18,934
you would've heard me say
that while there are guidelines,

89
00:07:19,038 --> 00:07:22,769
- a negotiator must be flexible.
- You gave the subject alcohol.

90
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:26,868
And you had some yourself.
Is that what you call being flexible, ma'am?

91
00:07:26,979 --> 00:07:28,003
Oh, sorry.

92
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:29,877
- Lieutenant.
- Lieutenant?

93
00:07:29,982 --> 00:07:32,348
Did you read the report, Officer?

94
00:07:33,085 --> 00:07:34,609
Because if you had, you might've noticed

95
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:37,814
that a sniper had his M4
trained on the subject.

96
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:40,684
- He could've missed.
- From 40 feet?

97
00:07:43,529 --> 00:07:47,625
The preservation of life is and will
always be the primary goal in negotiation.

98
00:07:47,733 --> 00:07:49,530
Everything else is secondary.

99
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:52,502
In this instance, I elected a face to face.

100
00:07:52,605 --> 00:07:54,505
I elected to give the subject a single beer

101
00:07:54,607 --> 00:07:57,804
because I thought these choices
would assist me in talking him down.

102
00:07:57,910 --> 00:08:02,074
That's a good strategy.
Unless he gets drunk and falls off the roof.

103
00:08:02,415 --> 00:08:03,712
Or you do.

104
00:08:04,450 --> 00:08:07,886
Maybe you get drunk off one beer, Officer,
but I don't.

105
00:08:13,593 --> 00:08:15,720
Can't you take the elevator
like a normal person?

106
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:18,422
And miss you struggling to keep up?

107
00:08:24,837 --> 00:08:25,895
What?

108
00:08:27,406 --> 00:08:29,567
It's that guy from yesterday.

109
00:08:30,776 --> 00:08:33,176
- Wonder what he wants.
- Who cares?

110
00:08:33,446 --> 00:08:36,244
Hot man, your office. Go.

111
00:08:44,657 --> 00:08:46,056
- Hi.
- Hi.

112
00:08:53,432 --> 00:08:54,421
So.

113
00:08:55,334 --> 00:08:58,565
Wow, this is where
a hostage negotiator works, huh?

114
00:09:02,275 --> 00:09:03,742
You have kids.

115
00:09:05,444 --> 00:09:07,378
Yeah, I have a daughter.

116
00:09:07,847 --> 00:09:09,838
So, what can I do for you?

117
00:09:11,117 --> 00:09:13,585
Actually I think I'm in some trouble.

118
00:09:13,686 --> 00:09:17,349
Had a dream last night that I was
sitting on the ledge in my underwear.

119
00:09:17,456 --> 00:09:19,583
- Boxers or briefs?
- Boxers.

120
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:22,926
Thought I might ask a professional
what this means.

121
00:09:23,029 --> 00:09:25,657
Maybe it means you should wear briefs.

122
00:09:26,032 --> 00:09:29,001
- You know I'm hitting on you, right?
- I'm a trained observer.

123
00:09:29,101 --> 00:09:31,729
So have dinner with me tomorrow night.

124
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:36,401
- What if I said I was suicidal?
- I'd say call the hotline.

125
00:09:37,443 --> 00:09:39,138
You're the hotline.

126
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:44,613
Drinks, tomorrow, 5:30.

127
00:09:45,718 --> 00:09:47,310
- 6:00.
- 5:45.

128
00:09:47,653 --> 00:09:50,850
My place, Swifty's.
It's on Fourth Street. I can pick you up.

129
00:09:50,957 --> 00:09:53,653
- I'll meet you there.
- Okay.

130
00:09:55,494 --> 00:09:56,984
Never seen him.

131
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:04,494
Roy called today.

132
00:10:05,071 --> 00:10:08,563
Great. Let me guess.
He's gonna be late with child support.

133
00:10:08,674 --> 00:10:11,768
Your ex- husband is an idiot,
I'll give you that.

134
00:10:12,411 --> 00:10:15,403
- What did the mechanic say?
- $600.

135
00:10:15,915 --> 00:10:18,213
- What about the ceiling?
- $400.

136
00:10:18,851 --> 00:10:20,375
And that's the good news.

137
00:10:20,486 --> 00:10:22,477
The plumber said we have to replace
all of our pipes.

138
00:10:22,588 --> 00:10:24,556
Don't even ask how much.

139
00:10:28,060 --> 00:10:32,292
Mom, when did you start having trouble
with the porch?

140
00:10:36,268 --> 00:10:39,965
I started having anxiety
about a month or two.

141
00:10:40,706 --> 00:10:44,472
I'm fine, Phoebe.
I have my chat rooms, online bridge, this.

142
00:10:44,577 --> 00:10:47,876
Stop worrying so much.
Tell me more about this date.

143
00:10:53,085 --> 00:10:55,952
So, are you gonna have a boyfriend?

144
00:10:59,392 --> 00:11:04,056
Kaitlyn's mom has a boyfriend.
She says it's a lot of work.

145
00:11:05,097 --> 00:11:08,191
Well, it can be a lot
of work, but then again,

146
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:11,895
Kaitlyn's mom is a little high- maintenance.

147
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:14,666
What's high- maintenance, Mama?

148
00:11:14,774 --> 00:11:18,938
It means she needs a lot of attention.
And don't you repeat that.

149
00:11:19,478 --> 00:11:20,775
Okay?

150
00:11:41,801 --> 00:11:45,828
I've been trying to figure out
why I can't get you out of my head.

151
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:48,869
It's the whole woman- carrying- a- gun thing.

152
00:11:48,974 --> 00:11:51,204
No, it's not.

153
00:11:51,343 --> 00:11:54,278
It's what you did with Joe out on the ledge.

154
00:11:54,814 --> 00:11:57,146
How did you know what to say to him?

155
00:11:57,249 --> 00:12:00,616
I don't know.
I guess I just watch a lot of TV, so...

156
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:04,553
- Okay, you're a smartass.
- Takes one to like one.

157
00:12:07,593 --> 00:12:10,721
How'd you get into this?
I mean, you don't seem...

158
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:13,458
- Like I fit the profile?
- Yeah.

159
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:17,100
It's my second year on the force,

160
00:12:17,203 --> 00:12:20,138
and my partner and I were
the first responders at the scene.

161
00:12:20,239 --> 00:12:23,106
- First squad car. And the HT had them...
- H... What?

162
00:12:23,209 --> 00:12:24,335
- Hostage- taker.
- Okay.

163
00:12:24,443 --> 00:12:27,810
He had his estranged wife
and three kids in there.

164
00:12:27,913 --> 00:12:32,680
I talked him down before backup arrived
and that was kind of when I decided

165
00:12:32,785 --> 00:12:34,650
- that's what I wanted to do.
- Wow.

166
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:38,349
What about you?
What you do takes a lot of work, I'm sure.

167
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:41,984
Owning a bar? No, not so much.

168
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:44,324
I mean, I was a bartender before, right.
I know the business.

169
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:46,398
Pour drinks, serve, thank you.

170
00:12:46,499 --> 00:12:48,990
I meant owning three bars

171
00:12:49,401 --> 00:12:52,666
and being a silent partner
in four downtown hotels.

172
00:12:55,641 --> 00:12:57,336
You googled me.

173
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:59,434
You know what the problem
with googling is?

174
00:12:59,545 --> 00:13:02,139
What, you might find out the man
you're going on a date with

175
00:13:02,248 --> 00:13:04,580
won $100 million in the lottery?

176
00:13:04,683 --> 00:13:07,208
- Yeah, that.
- Right, that.

177
00:13:08,387 --> 00:13:11,550
I was gonna say it takes
all the fun out of it.

178
00:13:13,225 --> 00:13:15,557
Is the money a plus or a minus?

179
00:13:15,995 --> 00:13:18,793
It's a plus that you didn't lead with it.

180
00:13:20,699 --> 00:13:23,133
Well, that's good because I was...

181
00:13:26,505 --> 00:13:28,097
- I gotta go.
- What?

182
00:13:28,207 --> 00:13:30,675
- Yeah.
- Hold on, hold on.

183
00:13:31,343 --> 00:13:33,834
Have dinner with me tomorrow night.

184
00:13:35,548 --> 00:13:39,211
Look, Duncan, despite your $100 million,

185
00:13:40,352 --> 00:13:44,220
I'm not really in a position
to start a relationship right now.

186
00:13:45,357 --> 00:13:47,587
Are you in a position to eat?

187
00:13:50,095 --> 00:13:52,757
What you gotta understand is
you are not in control here. I am in control.

188
00:13:52,865 --> 00:13:54,162
You're gonna put the gun down...

189
00:13:54,266 --> 00:13:56,700
Lieutenant. First responder's off the rails.

190
00:13:56,802 --> 00:13:58,793
He's been yelling at the HT.
He's got him all worked up.

191
00:13:58,904 --> 00:14:01,065
- Where's Tactical?
- Five away.

192
00:14:01,307 --> 00:14:02,934
Look, pal, this is getting ridiculous.

193
00:14:03,042 --> 00:14:04,634
We both know you're not gonna
shoot anyone.

194
00:14:04,743 --> 00:14:08,110
Why don't you call me back
when you're ready to talk?

195
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,175
Officer, situation?

196
00:14:12,017 --> 00:14:14,781
HT's name is Grady. Two hostages.
Witnesses heard gunfire.

197
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:17,048
When I arrived, he yelled out
if anybody tries to come in,

198
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:19,784
- he'll shoot them both.
- That's it?

199
00:14:19,892 --> 00:14:22,986
He says his lawyer cheated him
out of $10,000 and he wants it back.

200
00:14:23,095 --> 00:14:24,960
Who's working the log?

201
00:14:25,264 --> 00:14:27,255
Hey, I've been trying to keep this guy
from killing two people.

202
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:28,993
There hasn't been time for a log.

203
00:14:29,101 --> 00:14:31,001
Have you talked to any of the hostages?

204
00:14:31,103 --> 00:14:33,469
Do you know if anyone needs
medical attention?

205
00:14:33,572 --> 00:14:35,938
You're relieved.
Everything gets written down.

206
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:37,474
Get the HT on the phone.

207
00:14:37,576 --> 00:14:40,568
Hey, I'm the one keeping this
from blowing up.

208
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:44,248
- Hey.
- Hold it.

209
00:14:49,822 --> 00:14:51,517
- Yes?
- Mr. Grady?

210
00:14:51,824 --> 00:14:55,123
- Yes.
- This is Lieutenant Phoebe MacNamara.

211
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:57,422
Is that the way you people think
you can talk to me?

212
00:14:57,529 --> 00:14:59,520
- I have a gun.
- No, that was someone else.

213
00:14:59,632 --> 00:15:02,795
You'll be talking to me now.
Is everyone okay in there?

214
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:04,631
I don't wanna talk anymore.

215
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:07,433
No one is listening to me. No one cares.

216
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:10,300
I'm listening, Mr. Grady. I care.

217
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:12,104
No, you don't.

218
00:15:28,427 --> 00:15:29,917
Put that back.

219
00:15:38,037 --> 00:15:41,905
So, you did not call for backup,
you did not start a log,

220
00:15:42,007 --> 00:15:43,804
you did not ask about the hostages.

221
00:15:43,909 --> 00:15:45,877
Not to mention, you goaded the HT.

222
00:15:45,978 --> 00:15:47,377
I had it under control.

223
00:15:47,479 --> 00:15:51,108
I took statements from all the officers
on the scene and the hostages.

224
00:15:51,216 --> 00:15:53,514
They all described how you berated
the hostage- taker.

225
00:15:53,619 --> 00:15:55,712
You're just looking for someone to blame
for your screw up.

226
00:15:55,821 --> 00:15:58,187
My actions will hold up, Officer.

227
00:15:58,290 --> 00:15:59,587
Yours won't.

228
00:15:59,692 --> 00:16:01,956
You're suspended for 30 days.

229
00:16:02,061 --> 00:16:05,326
No, no, no, you are not running off
on me like this.

230
00:16:06,098 --> 00:16:07,690
You're free to protest the suspension,

231
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,030
but Captain McVee is
in complete agreement with me.

232
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:12,660
Which comes as no surprise,
considering you're doing him.

233
00:16:12,771 --> 00:16:14,966
I'm sorry, what did you just say?

234
00:16:15,074 --> 00:16:17,508
This is gonna get worse for you, bitch.

235
00:16:17,609 --> 00:16:18,633
That's a promise.

236
00:16:18,744 --> 00:16:20,735
Badge and weapon, Officer.

237
00:16:34,593 --> 00:16:37,357
I got it, I got it, I got it, I got it.

238
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:43,432
Hi. You must be Carly.

239
00:16:48,173 --> 00:16:49,140
Hi.

240
00:16:50,075 --> 00:16:52,566
- You look beautiful.
- Thanks.

241
00:16:53,312 --> 00:16:54,779
More flowers?

242
00:16:55,147 --> 00:16:57,945
Oh, yeah. Oh, no. These aren't for you.

243
00:16:59,184 --> 00:17:00,947
These are for you.

244
00:17:02,287 --> 00:17:03,447
Thanks.

245
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:05,520
Thank you.

246
00:17:06,158 --> 00:17:08,058
Duncan, this is my mother, Essie.

247
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,184
- Hi, Duncan.
- Hi.

248
00:17:09,294 --> 00:17:10,818
Would you like a drink?

249
00:17:10,929 --> 00:17:14,160
Oh, that's okay, Mom.
We should probably get going.

250
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:17,132
- Bye. I love you.
