285
00:18:58,537 --> 00:19:00,198
Ah, we have

286
00:19:01,406 --> 00:19:02,771
corn dogs,

287
00:19:04,676 --> 00:19:07,702
onion rings and "zee French fry."

288
00:19:10,349 --> 00:19:12,783
Well I have to say, I'm impressed.

289
00:19:13,285 --> 00:19:15,981
Really? I wasn't trying to impress you.

290
00:19:16,321 --> 00:19:17,788
Yes, you were.

291
00:19:20,726 --> 00:19:22,353
Wanna take a ride?

292
00:21:09,501 --> 00:21:14,200
Lieutenant? I might have to take a day off
later this week.

293
00:21:14,873 --> 00:21:17,967
- That's fine. Just let me know, okay?
- Lieutenant?

294
00:21:18,076 --> 00:21:21,204
- Annie, can it wait? I'm gonna be late, okay?
- I know, right.

295
00:21:21,313 --> 00:21:24,373
What I was gonna say is that,
I know I'm new here,

296
00:21:24,483 --> 00:21:28,647
- but I just I hope I'm doing a good job. So...
- You're doing great.

297
00:21:28,754 --> 00:21:29,721
Sorry.

298
00:22:07,893 --> 00:22:11,761
He came up behind me,
slammed me into the wall, disabled me.

299
00:22:12,597 --> 00:22:14,497
Did you see who it was?

300
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:17,199
He anticipated all my defense moves,

301
00:22:17,302 --> 00:22:20,669
knew how to use the cuffs,
knew where I'd have my piece.

302
00:22:20,772 --> 00:22:21,932
A cop?

303
00:22:22,474 --> 00:22:23,634
Meeks.

304
00:22:24,843 --> 00:22:27,744
Someone took the teddy bear
out of my office,

305
00:22:27,846 --> 00:22:30,212
left it mutilated on my front stoop.

306
00:22:30,315 --> 00:22:32,875
- What?
- He would've had access to it.

307
00:22:33,385 --> 00:22:36,912
Phoebe, I promise you, I will find
the son of a bitch who did this to you.

308
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:39,923
Now, if it was Meeks, I'll make sure he pays.

309
00:22:43,462 --> 00:22:45,089
I want you to take five days.

310
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:49,964
Now, let's pretend I said a week, you said
three, and we settled on five. Okay?

311
00:22:51,803 --> 00:22:53,964
Liz, make sure she gets home.

312
00:22:55,507 --> 00:22:59,500
Liz, I need somewhere to fall apart.
I can't do it at home.

313
00:22:59,611 --> 00:23:01,203
You can go to my place.

314
00:23:01,313 --> 00:23:03,440
I've got some family in town
but I'll get rid of them for the day.

315
00:23:03,548 --> 00:23:06,745
No. No, no, no, it's okay. I'll figure it out.

316
00:24:10,415 --> 00:24:11,939
How you doing?

317
00:24:19,257 --> 00:24:22,488
Look, I'm sorry to have just
dumped this on you.

318
00:24:23,528 --> 00:24:25,996
- I'm good to go.
- Will you stop?

319
00:24:26,097 --> 00:24:29,089
This is the best third date I've ever been on.

320
00:24:30,302 --> 00:24:31,997
Brought you some tea.

321
00:24:32,103 --> 00:24:35,903
And my own little personal remedy
for black eyes.

322
00:24:36,842 --> 00:24:39,367
I had to use it a few times myself.

323
00:24:47,752 --> 00:24:48,844
Hey.

324
00:24:49,654 --> 00:24:51,679
Where are you? Still here?

325
00:24:53,525 --> 00:24:57,757
Yeah, it's just, I was thinking
about the last time I felt like this.

326
00:24:59,364 --> 00:25:01,798
My dad was dead a couple of years.

327
00:25:02,567 --> 00:25:06,401
And my mother had a restraining order
against her boyfriend.

328
00:25:06,505 --> 00:25:08,735
He broke in one night with a shotgun.

329
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:12,037
Took my mother, my younger brother
and me hostage.

330
00:25:12,544 --> 00:25:17,277
The cops came and Dave, my boss now,
was the negotiator.

331
00:25:17,382 --> 00:25:19,213
And he talked him out?

332
00:25:20,285 --> 00:25:21,684
Not exactly.

333
00:25:22,020 --> 00:25:24,386
I put sleeping pills in his food.

334
00:25:25,357 --> 00:25:26,517
How old were you?

335
00:25:26,625 --> 00:25:27,819
Twelve.

336
00:25:30,061 --> 00:25:33,792
Well, I hope they put that guy away
for a long time.

337
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:37,062
Yeah, he died in prison a few years ago.

338
00:25:43,174 --> 00:25:46,769
You wanna tell me
what happened today, Phoebe?

339
00:25:49,814 --> 00:25:52,544
I got jumped in the stairwell at work.

340
00:25:52,651 --> 00:25:53,811
By who?

341
00:25:54,586 --> 00:25:57,487
Someone who has a problem
with my authority.

342
00:25:58,156 --> 00:26:00,283
Another cop did this to you?

343
00:26:02,327 --> 00:26:03,385
Who?

344
00:26:03,929 --> 00:26:06,056
I think I know,
but I don't have enough proof.

345
00:26:06,164 --> 00:26:09,190
- Just give me his name.
- Hey, I'm the cop.

346
00:26:10,368 --> 00:26:12,131
I'll do this my way.

347
00:26:22,113 --> 00:26:24,775
Look, I got to get back to the house.

348
00:26:26,651 --> 00:26:30,314
Are you gonna drive me home
or are you gonna make me walk?

349
00:26:44,569 --> 00:26:46,059
- What happened to your face?
- Mom, Mom.

350
00:26:46,171 --> 00:26:48,139
- What happened, Phoebe?
- Mom, I'm okay. It's okay, Mom.

351
00:26:48,239 --> 00:26:49,399
- Look at your lip!
- I'm okay.

352
00:26:49,507 --> 00:26:52,874
Mom, I can't have Carly down here.
Will you go check on her for me? Please?

353
00:26:52,978 --> 00:26:54,707
- Are you gonna be alright?
- Yeah, I'll be fine.

354
00:26:54,813 --> 00:26:57,441
- Please go check on her for me.
- Okay, I will but...

355
00:26:57,549 --> 00:26:59,949
Thanks, Mom. It's okay. It's okay.

356
00:27:04,856 --> 00:27:07,222
- You gonna be okay?
- Yeah.

357
00:27:10,729 --> 00:27:12,890
Thank you so much for today.

358
00:27:12,998 --> 00:27:16,661
You have no idea how much it helped me,
on so many levels.

359
00:27:17,168 --> 00:27:18,499
I can stay.

360
00:27:18,870 --> 00:27:20,360
On the couch.

361
00:27:23,575 --> 00:27:25,042
I'll be fine.

362
00:27:26,411 --> 00:27:28,845
Call me if you need anything, okay?

363
00:27:28,947 --> 00:27:30,346
- Okay.
- Okay.

364
00:27:35,954 --> 00:27:37,080
Feel better.

365
00:27:37,188 --> 00:27:38,883
- Thank you.
- Okay.

366
00:28:47,325 --> 00:28:49,793
Mama, can I sleep with you tonight?

367
00:28:49,894 --> 00:28:52,556
Of course you can, sweetheart. Come on.

368
00:28:57,001 --> 00:28:58,593
Come under here.

369
00:28:59,370 --> 00:29:02,533
- I like your PJs.
- I like yours.

370
00:29:02,774 --> 00:29:04,105
Come here.

371
00:29:07,812 --> 00:29:10,110
- Good night.
- Good night, Mommy.

372
00:29:10,615 --> 00:29:13,709
The mechanic called.
He said he could bring the car by later.

373
00:29:13,818 --> 00:29:16,218
The plumber can come Tuesday.

374
00:29:16,321 --> 00:29:18,016
Thank God for Visa.

375
00:29:18,857 --> 00:29:20,620
Duncan also called.

376
00:29:21,726 --> 00:29:24,160
He said he wants to know how you're doing.

377
00:29:24,262 --> 00:29:26,992
Can you tell me again
what happened to you?

378
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:31,701
Mommy fell running down the stairs,
sweetie.

379
00:29:33,004 --> 00:29:35,564
- How?
- I wasn't paying attention.

380
00:29:43,047 --> 00:29:44,105
Hey.

381
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:45,473
Wow.

382
00:29:46,751 --> 00:29:48,480
You look like crap.

383
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:51,847
Thanks. You should've seen it
before the makeup.

384
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:55,589
- Those from him?
- Yeah.

385
00:29:56,261 --> 00:29:57,819
And he made you tea.

386
00:29:57,929 --> 00:30:01,797
God, it's like you found a dodo bird.
Men like him are extinct.

387
00:30:02,433 --> 00:30:05,027
Yeah, I mean he's great, now.

388
00:30:06,371 --> 00:30:09,169
But sooner or later they all start to bark?

389
00:30:10,408 --> 00:30:12,899
We get to do our new jumps today.

390
00:30:13,011 --> 00:30:14,444
Oh, you do?

391
00:30:17,215 --> 00:30:19,615
Tell me you're arresting Arnie Meeks.

392
00:30:19,717 --> 00:30:21,582
Let's go over what happened again.

393
00:30:21,686 --> 00:30:23,847
Okay. I came in, dropped my stuff off.

394
00:30:23,955 --> 00:30:27,083
I was late, so I was rushing.
Headed downstairs.

395
00:30:27,192 --> 00:30:30,491
Did you stop anywhere, talk to anyone?

396
00:30:31,196 --> 00:30:32,220
No.

397
00:30:32,330 --> 00:30:33,922
Oh, yeah. Annie Utz.

398
00:30:34,032 --> 00:30:36,762
She just kept talking,
babbling on and on and on.

399
00:30:36,868 --> 00:30:39,200
What, like she was stalling you?

400
00:30:39,637 --> 00:30:44,131
Annie, we brought you in to talk about
what happened to Lieutenant MacNamara.

401
00:30:44,242 --> 00:30:46,107
I'm sorry she got hurt.

402
00:30:46,878 --> 00:30:50,211
You were the last one to talk to her
before she was attacked.

403
00:30:50,348 --> 00:30:51,508
Sorry.

404
00:30:52,584 --> 00:30:54,711
I'm really not feeling good.

405
00:30:55,053 --> 00:30:56,714
I think I might have to go home.

406
00:30:56,821 --> 00:31:00,154
Lieutenant MacNamara's
not feeling very well, either.

407
00:31:00,558 --> 00:31:04,654
Someone jumped me in the stairwell,
assaulted me, and handcuffed me.

408
00:31:05,330 --> 00:31:09,596
You kept talking to the Lieutenant
even after she said she'd be late.

409
00:31:09,968 --> 00:31:12,061
You set her up, didn't you?

410
00:31:13,204 --> 00:31:16,435
Annie, did you plan this with Meeks?

411
00:31:17,775 --> 00:31:19,436
Annie, look at me!

412
00:31:19,544 --> 00:31:20,977
Sorry.

413
00:31:21,980 --> 00:31:23,948
I'm sorry, I didn't know.

414
00:31:26,351 --> 00:31:30,913
He told me how you came onto him
and how he turned you down.

415
00:31:31,022 --> 00:31:34,185
He said he would've filed charges
but you were sleeping with the Captain.

416
00:31:34,292 --> 00:31:36,089
And you believed that?

417
00:31:39,530 --> 00:31:40,929
I'm sorry.

418
00:31:42,333 --> 00:31:45,666
He said he just needed
a few minutes to talk to you.

419
00:31:47,305 --> 00:31:48,772
I'm so sorry.

420
00:31:49,140 --> 00:31:52,837
My client stipulates that he
and Lieutenant MacNamara hold

421
00:31:53,278 --> 00:31:56,179
opposing viewpoints, professional styles.

422
00:31:56,281 --> 00:31:59,614
And that's hardly motive
for a physical attack on her person.

423
00:31:59,717 --> 00:32:01,446
Now, the lack of evidence here...

424
00:32:01,552 --> 00:32:05,044
You don't much like Lieutenant MacNamara,
do you, Arnie?

425
00:32:05,390 --> 00:32:06,448
No.

426
00:32:07,125 --> 00:32:09,889
Do you remember why you were
in her office last Thursday?

427
00:32:09,994 --> 00:32:11,359
Of course I do.

428
00:32:11,462 --> 00:32:13,327
She was covering her own ass
by suspending me

429
00:32:13,431 --> 00:32:16,423
after she screwed up
that hostage negotiation.

430
00:32:18,970 --> 00:32:21,438
First responder did not call for backup.

431
00:32:21,539 --> 00:32:24,702
Officer Meeks antagonized the HT
with threats. Also...

432
00:32:24,809 --> 00:32:26,970
Ask her who was on the phone with the HT
when he blew himself away.

433
00:32:27,078 --> 00:32:28,670
Look, you need...

434
00:32:29,647 --> 00:32:33,674
These are statements
from the other officers present at the scene.

435
00:32:34,352 --> 00:32:37,913
How long have you been cheating
on your wife with Annie Utz?

436
00:32:38,022 --> 00:32:40,855
She came onto me, I turned her down.
She's making this up.

437
00:32:40,959 --> 00:32:44,793
Funny. 'Cause Annie said that
you told her I came onto you.

438
00:32:45,596 --> 00:32:48,156
God, women just make your life a living hell.

439
00:32:48,266 --> 00:32:51,429
In fact, I'm actively restraining myself
from coming onto you right now.

440
00:32:51,536 --> 00:32:53,527
Keep it up, Detective,
and this interview is over.

441
00:32:53,638 --> 00:32:57,165
What kind of man lies in wait
like a snake in the grass, huh?

442
00:32:57,275 --> 00:32:59,675
You so afraid of her that
you had to jump her in the stairwell?

443
00:32:59,777 --> 00:33:01,574
I was never in that stairwell.

444
00:33:01,679 --> 00:33:03,169
Yes, you were.

445
00:33:05,817 --> 00:33:07,512
You know, you could've raped me,

446
00:33:07,618 --> 00:33:10,519
but I figured you knew you didn't have
what it takes to make an impression.

447
00:33:10,621 --> 00:33:12,213
All right, this interview is over.

448
00:33:12,323 --> 00:33:15,759
That's been a big problem in life for you,
hasn't it, Arnie?

449
00:33:15,860 --> 00:33:19,193
You can't back it up with the goods,
on the street, in the bedroom,

450
00:33:19,297 --> 00:33:22,528
or even in a stairwell where the only way
you could feel me up was to cuff me.

451
00:33:22,633 --> 00:33:25,261
You're lucky I didn't break your neck!

452
00:33:26,571 --> 00:33:29,472
Arnold Meeks, you're under arrest.

453
00:33:29,574 --> 00:33:32,236
Look, you can't arrest him.
You provoked him into saying that.

454
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:33,708
Watch me.

455
00:33:39,217 --> 00:33:40,878
Believe me, this isn't over.

456
00:33:40,985 --> 00:33:42,350
Let's go.

457
00:34:02,373 --> 00:34:05,536
Mom. Mom, it's okay.
Come on, let's go inside.

458
00:34:05,643 --> 00:34:08,510
- Phoebe.
- Come on, come on, let's go inside.

459
00:34:09,714 --> 00:34:10,772
I'm so sorry.

460
00:34:10,882 --> 00:34:13,373
- Hey, don't apologize, okay?
- I'm so sorry.

461
00:34:13,484 --> 00:34:16,783
Come on, let's sit down.
Come on. Come on, let's go.

462
00:34:23,561 --> 00:34:25,358
- I'm useless.
- No.

463
00:34:26,431 --> 00:34:29,025
You're hurt. We need groceries.

464
00:34:30,568 --> 00:34:32,536
Well, Domino's delivers.

465
00:34:33,304 --> 00:34:35,067
Come here. I'm okay.

466
00:34:35,873 --> 00:34:37,898
- I love you.
- I love you, too, Mom.

467
00:34:38,009 --> 00:34:39,306
I'm sorry.

468
00:34:39,410 --> 00:34:41,435
Hey, don't say you're sorry, okay?

469
00:34:41,546 --> 00:34:42,843
I'm sorry.

470
00:34:43,714 --> 00:34:46,512
It's okay. It's okay.

471
00:34:50,488 --> 00:34:51,785
What else?

472
00:34:52,757 --> 00:34:54,122
Yogurt.

473
00:35:03,534 --> 00:35:04,831
Next?

474
00:35:05,269 --> 00:35:06,497
Eggs.

475
00:35:09,674 --> 00:35:11,198
I didn't do it.

476
00:35:13,444 --> 00:35:14,934
Someone's gonna call the cops on me.

477
00:35:15,046 --> 00:35:16,843
Hey, I am the cops.

478
00:35:17,782 --> 00:35:19,215
Oh, good. Yeah.

479
00:35:19,317 --> 00:35:21,285
- You're safe.
- Thank you.

480
00:35:24,555 --> 00:35:26,819
Listen, I just... It doesn't...

481
00:35:27,725 --> 00:35:29,317
What's next?

482
00:35:29,994 --> 00:35:31,120
What's the matter?

483
00:35:31,229 --> 00:35:33,493
Nothing, I'm fine.
What was after eggs, though?

484
00:35:33,598 --> 00:35:36,499
- Wait, who is that?
- It's no one. It's no one.

485
00:35:36,601 --> 00:35:39,399
No, that's him, isn't
it? Why isn't he in jail?

486
00:35:39,504 --> 00:35:41,495
- It's called bail. Duncan, let it go.
- It's called bail?

487
00:35:41,606 --> 00:35:42,868
- Hey. Hey.
- Duncan!

488
00:35:42,974 --> 00:35:44,373
Hey, make you feel like a big guy
to jump on a woman?

489
00:35:44,475 --> 00:35:45,464
Duncan!

490
00:35:45,576 --> 00:35:47,874
