It seemed like the right thing to do.
He's in therapy.

974
01:10:24,653 --> 01:10:27,816
What? What are you thinking?

975
01:10:30,292 --> 01:10:32,556
How glad I am that I found you.

976
01:10:41,170 --> 01:10:43,798
You know what we need
when this is all over?

977
01:10:43,906 --> 01:10:45,100
What?

978
01:10:45,207 --> 01:10:46,538
A vacation.

979
01:10:46,675 --> 01:10:48,836
- A vacation?
- Yes, a vacation.

980
01:10:49,245 --> 01:10:50,405
Where?

981
01:10:52,214 --> 01:10:53,704
Disney World.

982
01:10:56,285 --> 01:10:58,651
Now that the psycho killer is caught,

983
01:10:58,754 --> 01:11:01,348
Phoebe and Duncan are
going to Disney World.

984
01:11:01,457 --> 01:11:02,822
And Carly.

985
01:11:03,092 --> 01:11:07,028
- Carly would love Disney World.
- You wanna take Carly to Disney World?

986
01:11:07,129 --> 01:11:10,155
Maybe just Carly, now that I think about it.

987
01:11:20,943 --> 01:11:22,103
Duncan.

988
01:11:25,414 --> 01:11:27,041
Will you marry me?

989
01:11:35,057 --> 01:11:36,684
Where's the ring?

990
01:11:37,826 --> 01:11:39,726
You don't have a ring?

991
01:11:40,496 --> 01:11:43,863
What kind of half- assed proposal is
this if you don't even have a ring?

992
01:11:43,966 --> 01:11:45,934
Well, been kind of busy.

993
01:11:46,035 --> 01:11:50,631
Yeah? I was gonna propose to you
at Disney World, but I would've had a ring.

994
01:11:52,041 --> 01:11:53,508
Is that a yes?

995
01:12:03,052 --> 01:12:04,144
Yes.

996
01:12:17,533 --> 01:12:19,194
- Hello.
- Hi.

997
01:12:19,635 --> 01:12:22,468
To what do I owe the honor
of a 10:00 a.m. phone call?

998
01:12:22,571 --> 01:12:24,971
Just wanted to see
if you had any plans for lunch.

999
01:12:25,074 --> 01:12:26,905
Well, I'm having lunch with Loo.

1000
01:12:27,009 --> 01:12:28,476
All right.

1001
01:12:28,811 --> 01:12:32,269
I guess you won't wanna help me
pick out a ring for Phoebe then, huh?

1002
01:12:32,381 --> 01:12:34,144
I can reschedule.

1003
01:12:34,350 --> 01:12:36,409
Yeah, I know my wallet's gonna regret this,

1004
01:12:36,518 --> 01:12:38,486
but bring Loo, too, okay?

1005
01:12:38,587 --> 01:12:40,487
Okay. Where're we doing this?

1006
01:12:40,589 --> 01:12:41,817
Mark D's.

1007
01:12:42,224 --> 01:12:45,091
What, did you win the lottery or something?

1008
01:12:45,427 --> 01:12:48,954
- How's noon?
- That works. Hey, Duncan,

1009
01:12:50,299 --> 01:12:51,926
you done good.

1010
01:12:52,034 --> 01:12:54,901
I know. Believe me, I know.

1011
01:12:57,873 --> 01:12:59,864
Any progress finding him?

1012
01:12:59,975 --> 01:13:04,139
He knows you saw him.
So he's got two options, cut and run

1013
01:13:04,246 --> 01:13:05,406
or finish this.

1014
01:13:05,514 --> 01:13:07,482
He's gonna finish it.

1015
01:13:07,816 --> 01:13:09,716
Are you ready for that?

1016
01:13:10,319 --> 01:13:12,378
Hey, Captain. Lieutenant.

1017
01:13:12,488 --> 01:13:15,286
Airport Budget said they rented
a car to a Samuel Grimes,

1018
01:13:15,391 --> 01:13:17,655
one- way with a drop- off in Middletown.

1019
01:13:17,760 --> 01:13:20,593
Here. Got a copy of the driver's license.

1020
01:13:27,569 --> 01:13:28,900
That's him.

1021
01:13:29,972 --> 01:13:32,031
Darker hair and glasses, but that's him.

1022
01:13:32,141 --> 01:13:34,837
- Address in Nevada?
- Yeah, but he paid with a Visa.

1023
01:13:34,943 --> 01:13:37,275
We've got a billing address
down on Tybee Avenue.

1024
01:13:37,379 --> 01:13:41,281
That's too easy. Why not just pay cash?
He knows we're gonna find this address.

1025
01:13:41,383 --> 01:13:43,351
He wants you to go there.

1026
01:13:44,086 --> 01:13:45,781
Phoebe, be careful.

1027
01:13:46,355 --> 01:13:48,983
Toothbrush and razor are still there.
He's not running.

1028
01:13:49,091 --> 01:13:51,150
No, but it doesn't mean he's coming back.

1029
01:13:51,260 --> 01:13:53,353
You're gonna wanna see this.

1030
01:13:58,267 --> 01:13:59,564
Holy crap.

1031
01:14:20,589 --> 01:14:22,079
It's real time.

1032
01:14:22,791 --> 01:14:23,951
Phoebe.

1033
01:14:25,227 --> 01:14:26,854
Timing mechanism.

1034
01:14:30,098 --> 01:14:31,429
No weapons.

1035
01:14:38,307 --> 01:14:40,639
No photos. Memory card's empty.

1036
01:14:42,344 --> 01:14:45,245
I think he's done here.
He knew we'd find this place.

1037
01:14:45,347 --> 01:14:47,508
Question is, where is he now?

1038
01:14:50,853 --> 01:14:53,048
Why photos of these locations?

1039
01:14:58,727 --> 01:14:59,785
Look.

1040
01:15:00,662 --> 01:15:03,256
Same photos on the laptop, same order.

1041
01:15:04,366 --> 01:15:06,766
Except these ones aren't up there.

1042
01:15:07,269 --> 01:15:10,966
And if he took them with him, they must
mean something, they must have a purpose.

1043
01:15:11,073 --> 01:15:12,631
They're targets.

1044
01:15:13,475 --> 01:15:15,306
Think he's giving himself the go?

1045
01:15:15,410 --> 01:15:16,775
Yeah, I do.

1046
01:15:17,279 --> 01:15:19,611
And it's gonna be today at noon.

1047
01:15:20,182 --> 01:15:21,911
Question is, where.

1048
01:15:22,351 --> 01:15:24,785
- Maybe it's the bank.
- Too obvious.

1049
01:15:26,188 --> 01:15:28,918
Look. It's that jewelry store, Mark D's.

1050
01:15:29,157 --> 01:15:31,284
It's not up there, either.

1051
01:15:31,393 --> 01:15:34,123
Yeah, it's romantic,
it sure as hell makes a statement,

1052
01:15:34,229 --> 01:15:36,629
and Angela's friend said he bought her
jewelry from there.

1053
01:15:36,732 --> 01:15:40,168
He's got a $3,000 charge from there
the month before Angela died.

1054
01:15:40,269 --> 01:15:42,032
That is a big item.

1055
01:15:42,137 --> 01:15:45,629
That's it. He proposed. Or he was going to.

1056
01:15:48,744 --> 01:15:50,268
Got 23 minutes.

1057
01:15:58,020 --> 01:15:58,987
We're early.

1058
01:15:59,087 --> 01:16:02,545
Okay. That means we can take
a couple laps before he gets here

1059
01:16:02,658 --> 01:16:03,647
and check out the good stuff.

1060
01:16:03,759 --> 01:16:05,386
- May I help you, ladies?
- Oh, yes.

1061
01:16:05,494 --> 01:16:09,396
Yes, please. I was thinking of
a gold- beaded pendant with diamonds.

1062
01:16:09,498 --> 01:16:11,466
Engagement rings, please.

1063
01:16:15,637 --> 01:16:17,400
Excuse me. Would you give me a moment?

1064
01:16:17,506 --> 01:16:18,632
Kevin.

1065
01:16:19,641 --> 01:16:21,541
Sorry. Engagement ring, right?

1066
01:16:21,643 --> 01:16:24,635
You've got to take the deliveries
around back.

1067
01:16:25,113 --> 01:16:26,808
I'll tell you what.

1068
01:16:29,084 --> 01:16:30,517
You!

1069
01:16:30,619 --> 01:16:32,143
- I didn't touch it.
- No?

1070
01:16:32,254 --> 01:16:34,347
Do it. Hit the alarm! Do it!

1071
01:16:36,358 --> 01:16:40,260
I want everyone to move to the back
of the store now. Everyone, move it.

1072
01:16:40,362 --> 01:16:42,057
Right there. Right there.

1073
01:16:42,164 --> 01:16:43,461
Now get on the floor.

1074
01:16:43,565 --> 01:16:46,363
Not you.
You, you move over here, right now. Now.

1075
01:16:46,468 --> 01:16:48,459
Now get down. Get down, right now.

1076
01:16:48,570 --> 01:16:51,061
Down. Empty your pockets and your purses.

1077
01:16:51,173 --> 01:16:52,162
Turn them inside out.

1078
01:16:52,274 --> 01:16:55,471
I want you to put the contents
on the floor in front of you, now.

1079
01:16:55,577 --> 01:16:59,274
Anyone reaches for a cell phone
or a weapon and this woman gets it.

1080
01:16:59,381 --> 01:17:02,316
Am I perfectly clear on that? Good.

1081
01:17:02,417 --> 01:17:05,181
You. Stand up. Stand up now!

1082
01:17:05,287 --> 01:17:07,847
If you hesitate again,
I will blow your head off.

1083
01:17:07,956 --> 01:17:10,083
Turn the alarm off. Do it.

1084
01:17:10,792 --> 01:17:12,419
Pick up the phone.

1085
01:17:12,961 --> 01:17:14,258
Dial 911.

1086
01:17:19,134 --> 01:17:21,830
This call came in four minutes ago,
Lieutenant.

1087
01:17:21,937 --> 01:17:23,097
This is Mark D.

1088
01:17:23,205 --> 01:17:26,697
There's an armed man holding me
and seven other people hostage in my store.

1089
01:17:26,808 --> 01:17:28,241
He has guns and explosives.

1090
01:17:28,343 --> 01:17:31,574
He says if he doesn't receive a phone call
from Lieutenant Phoebe MacNamara

1091
01:17:31,680 --> 01:17:34,547
by noon, he will shoot one of the hostages.

1092
01:17:38,286 --> 01:17:39,810
Take the alley.

1093
01:17:48,497 --> 01:17:50,863
Lieutenant, we're set up in here.

1094
01:17:53,068 --> 01:17:54,501
- Go, go, go!
- Let's go.

1095
01:17:54,603 --> 01:17:56,332
Get all your men to keep those people back.

1096
01:18:06,682 --> 01:18:08,445
We don't have his phone locked down yet.

1097
01:18:08,550 --> 01:18:10,177
What's the number?

1098
01:18:14,056 --> 01:18:17,514
Patch her line through the call box
as soon as you can.

1099
01:18:30,005 --> 01:18:31,302
Answer it.

1100
01:18:34,009 --> 01:18:36,307
Let me speak to the hostage taker.

1101
01:18:36,411 --> 01:18:37,810
It's for you.

1102
01:18:40,115 --> 01:18:41,480
Bring it here.

1103
01:18:45,487 --> 01:18:48,081
Jerry. How's everyone doing in there?

1104
01:18:49,057 --> 01:18:50,718
You know who I am.

1105
01:18:52,227 --> 01:18:54,252
Congratulations, Lieutenant.

1106
01:18:56,331 --> 01:18:58,196
Everyone's fine.

1107
01:18:58,300 --> 01:19:02,236
Except maybe the security guard.

1108
01:19:02,337 --> 01:19:04,669
You see, he's got on a new jacket,

1109
01:19:04,773 --> 01:19:08,607
and I don't think he likes it very much.

1110
01:19:10,746 --> 01:19:14,773
Are you saying you have explosives
strapped to the security guard?

1111
01:19:16,685 --> 01:19:18,676
God, you're quick, Phoebe.

1112
01:19:19,955 --> 01:19:22,423
Why don't we start with you releasing
some of the hostages?

1113
01:19:22,524 --> 01:19:23,491
No.

1114
01:19:24,392 --> 01:19:27,225
We'll start with the SWAT team
that have their rifles trained on me.

1115
01:19:27,329 --> 01:19:30,355
- You know the procedure.
- I sure as hell do, Lieutenant.

1116
01:19:30,465 --> 01:19:34,367
You get them to stand down right now
or I will shoot a hostage.

1117
01:19:35,837 --> 01:19:37,737
Get back to me in five.

1118
01:19:41,243 --> 01:19:43,234
Bravo 1, 2, 3, stand down.

1119
01:19:44,212 --> 01:19:45,304
Stand down.

1120
01:19:45,447 --> 01:19:47,039
Okay. I'm coming.

1121
01:19:47,883 --> 01:19:50,283
We got a partial visual, Lieutenant,
from the Sierra Team

1122
01:19:50,385 --> 01:19:52,410
on the second floor, adjacent building.

1123
01:19:52,521 --> 01:19:54,455
Five or six hostages.

1124
01:19:54,556 --> 01:19:57,525
Looks like there's a device
rigged to the rear door. What's our play?

1125
01:19:57,626 --> 01:20:01,357
- The other snipers in position?
- Two others, but they don't have a shot.

1126
01:20:01,463 --> 01:20:03,397
We have the green light?

1127
01:20:03,932 --> 01:20:06,662
He's gonna take himself and them with him.

1128
01:20:06,768 --> 01:20:08,599
- Phoebe, Phoebe. Phoebe.
- Duncan.

1129
01:20:08,703 --> 01:20:10,728
He knows two of the hostages.

1130
01:20:10,839 --> 01:20:13,603
- Ma Bee and Loo are in there.
- What? Are you sure?

1131
01:20:13,708 --> 01:20:17,109
They were supposed to meet me at noon.
I parked behind Loo's car.

1132
01:20:17,212 --> 01:20:18,907
They're smart women.
They won't do anything stupid.

1133
01:20:19,014 --> 01:20:20,072
What if he knows who they are?

1134
01:20:20,182 --> 01:20:22,844
There's no way he knew they were in there.
And he's not focusing on them.

1135
01:20:22,951 --> 01:20:26,978
You can get them out, right?
Right? Get him to let the women out?

1136
01:20:27,489 --> 01:20:28,649
Right?

1137
01:20:30,992 --> 01:20:32,857
Look, I need you to wait outside.

1138
01:20:32,961 --> 01:20:34,656
I gotta do my job.

1139
01:20:35,964 --> 01:20:37,192
Come on.

1140
01:21:00,222 --> 01:21:01,314
Yeah.

1141
01:21:01,690 --> 01:21:03,453
Is everyone okay in there?

1142
01:21:03,558 --> 01:21:05,458
Everyone's perfect, Lieutenant.

1143
01:21:05,560 --> 01:21:08,586
No one's laying on the floor
bleeding out because of you.

1144
01:21:08,697 --> 01:21:09,664
Not yet.

1145
01:21:12,100 --> 01:21:15,900
Is there anything I can get for you,
or anyone else in there?

1146
01:21:17,205 --> 01:21:19,298
You know I could've put that bomb
in your car.

1147
01:21:19,407 --> 01:21:20,840
I thought about it.

1148
01:21:20,942 --> 01:21:22,409
Why didn't you?

1149
01:21:22,510 --> 01:21:27,209
Because then you wouldn't be here
talking with me right now, you stupid bitch.

1150
01:21:28,316 --> 01:21:31,342
Okay, look, what can I do to help
resolve this situation, Jerry?

1151
01:21:31,453 --> 01:21:34,889
Stick your gun in your mouth
and pull the trigger, that's what.

1152
01:21:34,990 --> 01:21:37,356
I thought you wanted
to talk this through with me.

1153
01:21:37,459 --> 01:21:41,589
I know you have things to say to me.
I'm here to listen to you.

1154
01:21:41,696 --> 01:21:43,926
Or do you wanna talk to someone else?

1155
01:21:44,032 --> 01:21:45,397
You let her die.

1156
01:21:45,500 --> 01:21:48,992
I had the kill shot.
All you had to do was green light.

1157
01:21:50,705 --> 01:21:52,639
I know you blame me for Angela's death.

1158
01:21:52,741 --> 01:21:54,470
I know how you feel.

1159
01:21:54,943 --> 01:21:57,275
But we didn't know Angela was hurt
in the first hour.

1160
01:21:57,379 --> 01:21:59,006
You should have.

1161
01:22:03,885 --> 01:22:06,183
He's still in the northeast corner
of the store, here.

1162
01:22:06,288 --> 01:22:07,755
We don't have a shot unless he moves.

1163
01:22:07,856 --> 01:22:09,346
And then we're shooting through
half- inch glass,

1164
01:22:09,457 --> 01:22:10,947
and that'll affect the trajectory.

1165
01:22:11,059 --> 01:22:12,686
- We could hit a hostage.
- Yeah.

1166
01:22:12,794 --> 01:22:16,286
We need one shot to take out the glass,
the other the HT.

1167
01:22:16,398 --> 01:22:18,662
My explosive guys have looked
at that rig at the rear door.

1168
01:22:18,767 --> 01:22:21,600
They think they can defuse it
and circumvent the alarm.

1169
01:22:21,703 --> 01:22:24,399
- But they don't know.
- Pretty damn sure.

1170
01:22:26,341 --> 01:22:27,501
I'll give you an hour,

1171
01:22:27,609 --> 01:22:31,045
then I'm gonna let the bomb squad
take that rig and go through the rear door.

1172
01:23:00,909 --> 01:23:03,742
It's been over an hour
and there's been very little movement.

1173
01:23:03,845 --> 01:23:07,144
We understand there are
at least seven hostages in the store.

1174
01:23:07,248 --> 01:23:09,876
Mark D's is a high- end jewelry store

1175
01:23:09,985 --> 01:23:13,113
here in one of the city's most trendy
shopping districts.

1176
01:23:19,294 --> 01:23:20,420
Jerry?

1177
01:23:21,429 --> 01:23:23,795
Not much fun just waiting, is it?

1178
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:27,969
There's absolutely nothing that you can do.

1179
01:23:28,069 --> 01:23:30,697
Have you thought about what you want?

1180
01:23:31,806 --> 01:23:33,239
$10 million.

1181
01:23:35,677 --> 01:23:39,613
Okay, I can get that started
if you release the female hostages.

1182
01:23:40,482 --> 01:23:42,643
Send out the female hostages.

1183
01:23:48,089 --> 01:23:49,681
You didn't care about the women hostages

1184
01:23:49,791 --> 01:23:52,885
when you let Angela bleed to death,
did you?

1185
01:23:52,994 --> 01:23:55,963
Did you? No. No.

1186
01:23:56,064 --> 01:23:58,589
You're gonna do something for me, first.

1187
01:23:58,700 --> 01:24:00,895
You're gonna go in front
of those cameras out there

1188
01:24:01,002 --> 01:24:04,267
and you're gonna make a statement about
how you're responsible for Angela's death.

1189
01:24:04,372 --> 01:24:07,967
Then we'll talk about releasing
the female hostages.

1190
01:24:10,678 --> 01:24:11,940
Lieutenant, I'm moving my men into...

1191
01:24:12,047 --> 01:24:14,038
That your backup, Phoebe?

1192
01:24:14,516 --> 01:24:17,542
You getting some pressure
to move things along?

1193
01:24:18,987 --> 01:24:22,548
So you'll release the hostages
if I make a statement.

1194
01:24:22,657 --> 01:24:24,249
No, I think I've got a better idea.

1195
01:24:24,359 --> 01:24:25,383
You come in here

1196
01:24:25,493 --> 01:24:29,293
and you give that statement
in front of me on my camera phone,

1197
01:24:29,397 --> 01:24:31,797
and I'll let all the hostages go.

1198
01:24:32,967 --> 01:24:36,130
I come in, and you'll
let all the hostages go.

1199
01:24:36,471 --> 01:24:37,597
Yeah.

1200
01:24:40,508 --> 01:24:42,442
That's not gonna happen.

1201
01:24:55,890 --> 01:24:58,051
- Do you want me to try and stop...
- No.

1202
01:24:58,159 --> 01:24:59,990
Whatever you say, sir.

1203
01:25:02,030 --> 01:25:03,793
Give me the log book.

1204
01:25:08,303 --> 01:25:10,328
Liz, I need a pink rose.

1205
01:25:10,438 --> 01:25:13,236
There's a florist half a block down 16th.

1206
01:25:15,677 --> 01:25:17,406
She's coming out.

1207
01:25:27,188 --> 01:25:29,486
Okay, I'm in the street, Jerry.

1208
01:25:34,696 --> 01:25:37,096
They just gave me Angela's diary.

1209
01:25:38,566 --> 01:25:39,999
You're lying.

1210
01:25:40,568 --> 01:25:42,502
She didn't have a diary.

1211
01:25:42,804 --> 01:25:45,932
It's right here. I just
got it out of Evidence.

1212
01:25:47,909 --> 01:25:49,376
Read it to me.

1213
01:25:49,878 --> 01:25:52,369
Read it so I know you're not lying.

1214
01:25:57,285 --> 01:25:59,583
She's got a rose pressed in the pages here.

1215
01:25:59,687 --> 01:26:02,247
Just read it so I can hear her words.

1216
01:26:03,725 --> 01:26:06,888
Quid pro quo, Jerry.
You gotta get me some hostages.

1217
01:26:06,995 --> 01:26:08,826
You read it right now.

1218
01:26:13,168 --> 01:26:14,999
